==English==
===Etymology===
originally, a rushed sacrament of confession ([[shrift]]) given to a prisoner who was to be executed very soon
===Pronunciation===
(US) IPA: /ˌʃɔrt ˈʃrɪft/
===Noun===
'''[[short]] [[shrift]]'''
# a [[quick]] [[rejection]] of an idea or a person, often without given them the consideration they deserve
#*The bank gave me short shrift when I applied for a loan.